### Final Mathematical Formulations of the 11 Axioms


#### Global Definitions & Calibration Protocol
- **Thresholds**: Literature-specific where available; otherwise 90th percentile from 100 phase-randomized surrogates (Theiler et al., 1992).
- **Surrogates**: Phase-randomized Fourier (preserves power, destroys phase/rhythm) or amplitude-adjusted Fourier (AAFT) for nonlinear tests.
- **Statistical Test**: Wilcoxon rank-sum vs. surrogates, reject H‚ÇÄ at p<0.05.
- **Units**: Dimensionless; series z-scored.
- **Multi-entity Note**: For axioms requiring multiple networks (9‚Äì10), use external pairing (e.g., load paired CSVs); univariate proxies provided for Fracttalix compatibility.

1. **Matter and energy spontaneously form networks**  
   **Formulation**: Clustering coefficient CC > CC_random + 0.1 (Barab√°si network benchmark). Flux F = var(‚àáR) > 0.  
   **H‚ÇÄ**: CC ‚â§ CC_random + 0.1 (Wilcoxon p‚â•0.05).  
   **Test**: 2D lattice Ising near critical T.  
   **Counterexample**: Isolated particles.  
   **Pilot**: N/A (simulation).

2. **Networks store resources to buffer entropy**  
   **Formulation**: I(network; resources) > I(isolated; resources) + 0.1 bits (Cover & Thomas, 1991 benchmark).  
   **H‚ÇÄ**: I_network ‚â§ I_isolated + 0.1 (p‚â•0.05).  
   **Test**: Barab√°si‚ÄìAlbert vs. disconnected on resource histogram.  
   **Counterexample**: Noisy complete graph.  
   **Pilot**: N/A (simulation).

3. **Resource storage tends to increase in complexity**  
   **Formulation**: h_Œº > 0.05 bits/symbol (Grassberger, 1989 symbolic dynamics).  
   **H‚ÇÄ**: h_Œº ‚â§ 0.05 (p‚â•0.05).  
   **Test**: Evolving storage sequences.  
   **Counterexample**: Fixed storage.  
   **Pilot**: N/A (simulation).

4. **Complex emergent behaviors arise as storage capacity grows**  
   **Formulation**: Giant component œÜ jumps >0.5 at p_c ‚âà 1/(‚ü®k‚ü©-1) (Erd≈ës‚ÄìR√©nyi, 1960).  
   **H‚ÇÄ**: No discontinuous jump.  
   **Test**: Erd≈ës‚ÄìR√©nyi varying p.  
   **Counterexample**: Subcritical p.  
   **Pilot**: N/A (simulation).

5. **Information is encoded in structure (spatial) and rhythm (temporal)**  
   **Formulation**: I_total ‚â• I_spatial + I_temporal - overlap, overlap ‚â§20% (dual-channel EEG studies, e.g., Stam 2007).  
   **H‚ÇÄ**: I_total ‚âà max(I_spatial, I_temporal) (p‚â•0.05).  
   **Test**: Fractal + oscillatory vs. noise.  
   **Counterexample**: White noise.  
   **Pilot**: Bitcoin returns (I_total > max, dual encoding).

6. **Functional networks display rhythmic patterns; absence suggests dormancy**  
   **Formulation**: R = max(P(f))/total power > 0.1 (chronobiology dominant peak, Buzs√°ki 2006).  
   **H‚ÇÄ**: R identical active/dormant (p‚â•0.05).  
   **Test**: Periodic vs. broadband.  
   **Counterexample**: Chaotic logistic.  
   **Pilot**: HRV awake vs. sleep (R high awake).

7. **Dormant/disrupted networks cascade to sub-networks until rhythm resumes**  
   **Formulation**: P(s) ~ s^{-Œ±} (1.5 ‚â§ Œ± ‚â§ 2, Bak SOC range) during disruption; ends R > 0.1.  
   **H‚ÇÄ**: Exponential decay (p‚â•0.05 goodness-of-fit).  
   **Test**: Sandpile model.  
   **Counterexample**: Overdamped linear.  
   **Pilot**: N/A (simulation).

8. **Many networks exhibit fractal self-similarity across scales**  
   **Formulation**: |D_full - D_sub| < 0.1 across subscales (West scaling laws).  
   **H‚ÇÄ**: Variation >0.1 (p‚â•0.05).  
   **Test**: Higuchi full vs. windows.  
   **Counterexample**: Pure sine.  
   **Pilot**: Bitcoin (D consistent ~1.5).

9. **Networks interconnect laterally, temporally, and fractally**  
   **Formulation**: C_ms > 0.5 (multi-scale wavelet coherence, Grinsted 2004). Univariate proxy: coherence across window sizes.  
   **H‚ÇÄ**: C_ms ‚â§ surrogate (p‚â•0.05).  
   **Test**: Hierarchical vs. flat.  
   **Counterexample**: Disconnected modules.  
   **Pilot**: Multi-sensor HRV (high C_ms).

10. **Compatible networks tend to synchronize rhythms**  
    **Formulation**: Kuramoto r ‚Üí1 when Œîœâ < K (Strogatz 2000). Univariate proxy: high autocorr consistency.  
    **H‚ÇÄ**: r identical regardless Œîœâ (p‚â•0.05).  
    **Test**: Coupled oscillators.  
    **Counterexample**: Detuned frequencies.  
    **Pilot**: Paired EEG channels (high r compatible).

11. **Stressors trigger cascades followed by reorganization at higher resilience**  
    **Formulation**: H_post > H_pre + 0.1 and T_rec < median pre-stress (Holling resilience).  
    **H‚ÇÄ**: No gain/slow recovery (p‚â•0.05).  
    **Test**: Volatility injection pre/post.  
    **Counterexample**: Brittle system.  
    **Pilot**: Bitcoin 2022 crash (H_post gain post-reorg).

